The Trump Administration is focused on modernizing the nation's infrastructure, including water projects. They have implemented a One Federal Decision policy to improve coordination between federal agencies on environmental reviews for major infrastructure projects. President Trump has directed agencies to expedite ongoing environmental reviews in the western United States to meet the demands of water users, reduce flood risks, and generate hydropower. On National Hydropower Day, officials from the U.S. Bureau of Reclamation, the U.S. Department of Energy, and the U.S. Army Corps of Engineers are signing a Memorandum of Understanding to collaborate on hydropower technology research and development. Hydropower provides clean, renewable, reliable, and affordable energy for millions of American homes and helps balance energy grids. The development of modern infrastructure, including hydropower facilities, is a priority for the administration. They are working to streamline regulations and improve coordination between federal agencies to support the development of water projects and other infrastructure.